## VERIFIED MICHIGAN DATA SOURCES (Live API Endpoints)

### 1. SEMCOG Sidewalks & Crosswalks (Southeast Michigan — 7 counties)

This is the highest-value immediate data source. SEMCOG has a production ArcGIS FeatureServer with sidewalk and crosswalk data for Wayne, Oakland, Macomb, Washtenaw, Livingston, Monroe, and St. Clair counties.

- **FeatureServer REST API:** `https://gis.semcog.org/server/rest/services/Hosted/Sidewalks_and_Crosswalks/FeatureServer`
- **Layer 0 (Sidewalks):** `https://gis.semcog.org/server/rest/services/Hosted/Sidewalks_and_Crosswalks/FeatureServer/0`
- **Layer 1 (Crosswalks):** `https://gis.semcog.org/server/rest/services/Hosted/Sidewalks_and_Crosswalks/FeatureServer/1`
- **Query example (GeoJSON):** `https://gis.semcog.org/server/rest/services/Hosted/Sidewalks_and_Crosswalks/FeatureServer/0/query?where=1%3D1&outFields=*&f=geojson&resultRecordCount=100`
- **Created:** 2019 using AI-digitized aerial imagery
- **Updated:** Quarterly by SEMCOG staff
- **Open Data Portal:** `https://maps-semcog.opendata.arcgis.com/`
- **Limitation:** Does NOT capture condition or quality — only presence/absence and geometry

### 2. SEMCOG Bicycle & Pedestrian Mobility Network

- **Interactive Maps Hub:** `https://bicycle-and-pedestrian-mobility-maps-semcog.hub.arcgis.com/`
